questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a high-throughput Spring Boot application deployed on Tomcat experiences a gradual degradation in performance, culminating in an `OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space` after several hours. The application processes transactions using a standard thread pool. You find the following snippet in a core service:

java
@Service
public class TransactionLogger {
    private final ThreadLocal<byte[]> transactionBuffer = new ThreadLocal<>();

    @Transactional
    public void logTransaction(Transaction tx) {
        byte[] data = preparePayload(tx);
        transactionBuffer.set(data);
        processPayload(data);
        if (tx.hasErrors()) {
            throw new TransactionException("Failed to process");
        }
        transactionBuffer.remove();
    }
}

Heap analysis indicates that millions of `byte[]` arrays are retained in memory, even though active concurrent requests are very low.
